	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=20101&mid=106741916839010>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=20101&mid=106741916839010>All Fine</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=20101&mid=106741916839010#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 29th 4:19 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2553><span id=Scholar>Walkka</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.11]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All the classes listed above should have a chance on the shield. Probably none will use it all the time but all will have a use for it.<br><br>As a warrior I went 65 levels and 4 years without a shield, I know now it has become something to put on my priority list, if only to use the /shield ability more effectively.<br><br>Or if I can keep agro with only a good main hand weapon, then why not use the extra AC ans stats of the shield? Warriors arent the dps in a group so as long as I keep the agro its fine. Same goes for Paladins / SK when tanking. <br><br>Rangers enjoy the stats as they use their bow, and so do rogues who rely mostly on their main hand to dps.<br><br>The more I look at it the better I find this item. It might be a little weak considering the zone, but then it's not dropped by a raid boss either!<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Oct 29 04:32:11 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Walkka Walhalla<br>Warrior of 65 trains on Sebilis</td></td></tr>
